</p></div>"}

Tie another knot after winding, then either tape around this or glue to ensure it stays in place. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bd/Make-a-Fishing-Game-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-a-Fishing-Game-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bd/Make-a-Fishing-Game-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-a-Fishing-Game-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
